# Bunny Stream Webhook Authentication
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Bunny Stream's webhook UI does NOT expose a signing-secret field today, so
# we authenticate via a token in the URL query string + the account-specific
# VideoLibraryId echoed in every webhook body.
#
# 1. Generate a strong random token (32 bytes hex is fine):
#      node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
# 2. Set it here:
BUNNY_WEBHOOK_TOKEN=your_random_hex_here
# 3. Configure Bunny Stream's webhook URL as:
#      https://api.mulhimiq.com/api/webhooks/bunny/video-status?token=<BUNNY_WEBHOOK_TOKEN>
#
# SAFETY: when NODE_ENV=production AND this env is unset, ALL unsigned
# webhooks are refused (no silent downgrade to libraryId-only).

# (Optional) Comma-separated IP allowlist for Bunny's outbound webhooks.
# Leave unset until Bunny publishes a stable outbound IP range.
# BUNNY_WEBHOOK_ALLOWED_IPS=

# (Optional) Hide a test teacher from all students except one allowlisted
# student. Defaults match the MulhimIQ test accounts when unset.
# HIDDEN_TEACHER_EMAIL=www.sjad.n@gmail.com
# HIDDEN_TEACHER_VISIBLE_TO_STUDENT_EMAIL=mulhimiq@gmail.com
